column2: A gene is a sequence of DNA that contains the instructions for making a specific protein or RNA molecule. Genes are the basic units of heredity and are responsible for determining the traits of an organism.
column2_LT: Genēs yra genomedija, kuriame eso įrašai skėtų bei atvejų galvintojo nusprendimą. Genēs yra aukštai žančios, kuriose esote ir gaminėje pripažoma savora taurės organismo pasirūdojimas.
column2_EN: Genes are genetics, which involves deciding what to express and what not based on the information in the genetic material. Genes are high-level molecules that contain the flavor of the organism's tissues and organs.

column2: The cell is the fundamental structural and functional unit of life. All living organisms are made up of cells, which can be unicellular (single-celled organisms) or multicellular (such as plants and animals).
column2_LT: Įtis ir taurinės sūduotių bei visuomenės sūdudimui išveidytas iškildeis. Visi lifeo biologios atlieka iš įtis, kurios yra vienakalnio kūnas (ikiškilnojo organismai) ar devynkalnio (tik pagamynės ir gyvavęs gyvenuvolys).
column1_EN: Cellas is an epithet of several Greek heroes in Greek mythology
column2_EN: It is the instinct and natural instincts as well as to every society's customs are revealed. All life forms biologists follow which are one body shape (if it is a unicellular organism) or ten-organism (if it is an animal living in a population).

column2: DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) is a molecule that carries the genetic instructions used in the growth, development, and functioning of all living organisms. It consists of two strands that coil around each other to form a double helix.
column2_LT: DNA (deoxyribonukleikės acidių molsīvas) yra molekula, kuria apie jis pagaminta geninis duomenų konsignavimas, kurioslaukiu ir gydendiamas kaip visi Žemyno žymūnai. Jį skrytė du briedžiai.
column2_EN: DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) is a molecule that holds genetic information which is consigned and encoded into it like all human genomes. It was deciphered by two scientists.

column2: RNA (ribonucleic acid) is a molecule similar to DNA but typically single-stranded. RNA plays a key role in translating the genetic information from DNA into proteins, with types such as mRNA, tRNA, and rRNA.
column2_LT: RN (riboksneiksidnikas akasas) yra moleculeų lygiai similėrai daugelui, kad jis įraša genetiną informaciją dažnai būkstelėms proteinams, svarbiaus konkretoje priamboji type ir tās priejų, kaip mRNA, tRNA, ir rRNA.
column1_EN: nucleic acids are living things and DNA
column2_EN: Ribonucleic acid RN is closely related to many molecules and often encodes genetic information for proteins of a particular class and its relatives such as messenger RNA, transfer RNA, and ribosomal RNA.

column2: Proteins are large, complex molecules made up of amino acids. They perform a vast array of functions within organisms, including catalyzing reactions (enzymes), providing structure to cells, and regulating biological processes.
column2_LT: Proteinas ir tarpiais, svarbūs bei skėtų molekulai, atvadindas amoniakonidai. Jie esu skaidrantos radionuklėjų geros pateikimo reišdos (enzimai), skleidyjuo kaimus ir antykuriškius biologijos procesus.
column2_EN: Proteins are important and useful biomolecules that serve as the building blocks for other molecules, such as enzymes, fats, and sugars. They provide a source of energy (enzymes) to our cells, help construct our homes (fats), and facilitate various biological processes.

column2: Enzymes are biological catalysts that speed up chemical reactions in living organisms. They are typically proteins that lower the activation energy of a reaction, allowing it to proceed more quickly and efficiently.
column2_LT: Enzimai biologinė katalytinius, kurie pagrindoti gausią chemiską reaksiją i gyvų organizmą. Jie yra skaitomoji proteinai, kurios kaimas atsakaite energijos būtymą i tebe pereitėma reaktuui atlikdami ją geriausiai.
column2_EN: Enzymes are biological catalysts which regulate a numerous chemical reaction and the living organism they are part of; they are composed of proteins that take in energy, and then transform it into reactions that occur more efficiently.

column2: Lipids are a diverse group of hydrophobic or amphipathic molecules that include fats, oils, phospholipids, and sterols. They serve as energy storage, structural components of cell membranes, and signaling molecules, and are essential for maintaining cell integrity and function.
column2_LT: Lipidai yje duoks grupė, kuria dažnai pastaros, oksaidinių naudojimą, akampos naudojimo, ir parydamsuoto juos, taip kūrėtos bāzės, ir geriu noruo ir laikaus atlikymą.
column1_EN: Lipidas is a genus of beetles commonly known as field click beetles
column2_EN: Lipidai yje duoks grupė, kuria dažnai pastaros, oksaidinių naudojimą, akampos naudojimo, ir parydamsuoto juos, taip kūrėtos bāzės, ir geriu noruo ir laikaus atlikymą

column2: A glycan is a carbohydrate or saccharide, typically a polymer of sugar molecules, that can be attached to proteins or lipids in the form of glycosylation. Glycans are involved in a variety of biological processes, including cell-cell communication, immune response, and protein folding.
column2_LT: Glykanas yra karbonilų ar saccharidų polimernis, kuriame dažnai labai yra suguosas kitių suguoses, kurios gali būti atsudertiukomis formojose glykosiškių, ikių. Glykanai susitaiko bendrius ir imunitų antiprodukciją, aktyvosios ir proteinos pakartėjimą.
column2_EN: Glycans are carbohydrate polymers containing many water-containing other water-containing compounds which can be highly soluble in glycosylases until they can form glycoproteins. Glycans assemble together with immune system and antiproliferative activity proteins.

column2: A chromosome is a long, thread-like structure made of DNA and proteins. It carries the genetic information of an organism, and humans have 23 pairs of chromosomes in their cells.
column2_LT: Chromonas ir labdai laikas yra duomės ir proteinų skaidykliu sudaryta, kuria įvedydą informaciją vienas organizmas, žemai yra 23 pairs chromosome nuo telo.
column2_EN: Chromonas ir labdai laikas yra duomės ir proteinų skaidykliu sudaryta, kuria įvedydą informaciją vienas organizmas, žemai yra 23 pairs chromosome nuo telo.

column2: Mitochondria are organelles found in eukaryotic cells that are responsible for producing energy in the form of ATP. Often called the 'powerhouses' of the cell, mitochondria also play a role in regulating the cell cycle and cell growth.
column1_LT: Mitochondria suka išsamai šaltų medžių ir energijos.
column2_LT: Mitochondrionai yje biotikratinių pereitamo į mūsų organismus, kurios daryti energiją forma ATP. Kaip gaminiai, atliekianti siauką, mitochondriai kaip „energetinių kaimu“, yje atvejau iki susivykdo jų ionicų ir mechanizmuų.
column1_EN: Mitochondria prefer a cold and nutrient-rich environment.
column2_EN: Mitochondria bring biotin to us organisms which give energy in the form of ATP. Like games they keep ions and mechanisms active until they dissolve.
